setNA <- function(x, new) ifelse(is.na(x), new, x)
wateryear <- function(d) year(d) + ifelse(month(d) %in% 10:12, 1, 0)
toNumber <- function(x) as.numeric(paste(x))
Mean <- function(x) ifelse(all(is.na(x)), NA, mean(x, na.rm = TRUE))

scale_x_origin <- function(...) {
  scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.05)), limits = c(0,NA), ...) }
scale_y_origin <- function(...) {
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.05)), limits = c(0,NA), ...) }

Load data

## Levee failures
failures <- 
  read.csv('C:/Users/cbowers/Downloads/flood_sheet2.csv', header = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(Date = mdy(Date), wy = wateryear(Date)) %>% 
  mutate(
    type2 = case_match(
      .x = type,  
      c('Limited height', 'Wetland', 'Suisun Marsh') ~ 'Restricted height',
      'Agricultural Project levee' ~ 'Agricultural',
      .default = type),
    condition = case_match(
      .x = condition, 
      'No failure' ~ 'Averted failure',
      .default = condition) %>% 
      gsub(' failure', '', .) %>% 
      factor(levels = c('Averted', 'Temporary', 'Permanent')))


## keep only AR-induced failures
failures.lite <- failures %>% 
  filter(other_cause == '' & month(Date) %in% c(10:12,1:3)) %>% 
  arrange(Date) %>% 
  mutate(id = 1:nrow(.))
## AR days
ardays <- 
  read_csv('C:/Users/cbowers/Downloads/CA_landfall_mod4excel copy.csv', show_col_types = FALSE) %>% 
  # keep only ARs that landed in Sac and SJ watersheds 
  filter(lfloc_lat > 36 & lfloc_lat < 41.5, lfloc_lon > 230 & lfloc_lon < 240) %>% 
  transmute(
    date = ymd(paste(Year, Month, Day)),
    lon = lfloc_lon - 360, lat = lfloc_lat,
    ivt = Total_IVT) %>% 
  group_by(date) %>% 
  reframe(across(everything(), ~.[which.max(ivt)])) %>% 
  # keep only days that meet AR threshold criteria
  filter(ivt > 250) %>%
  mutate(
    wy = wateryear(date),
    bucket = cut(ivt, breaks = c(250*(1:5),5000), labels = 250*(1:5)),
    watershed = ifelse(lat > 38.5, 'Sacramento', 'San Joaquin')) %>%
  mutate(id = 1:nrow(.))

AR & failures by WY

data <- failures.lite %>% 
  filter(wateryear(Date) > 1980) %>% 
  count(wy = wateryear(Date), condition, name = 'failures') %>% 
  group_by(wy) %>% 
  summarize(
    failed = sum(failures[condition != 'Averted']), 
    averted = sum(failures[condition == 'Averted'])) %>% 
  full_join(ardays %>% count(wy = wateryear(date), name = 'ardays') %>% filter(wy > 1980), by = 'wy') %>% 
  mutate(across(c(failed, averted), ~setNA(.x,0))) %>% 
  mutate(total = failed + averted)

## what percentage of levees have an AR before them?

g <- failures.lag %>% 
  filter(lag <= 30) %>% 
  group_by(lag) %>% 
  reframe(
    pct1 = sum(!is.na(nearest1))/length(lag),
    pct2 = sum(!is.na(nearest2))/length(lag),
    pct3 = sum(!is.na(nearest3))/length(lag),
    pct4 = sum(!is.na(nearest4))/length(lag),
    pct5 = sum(!is.na(nearest5))/length(lag)) %>% 
  ggplot() + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = 14, color = 'grey50', linetype = 'dashed') + 
  geom_line(aes(x = lag, y = pct5, color = '5'), size = 0.75) + 
  geom_line(aes(x = lag, y = pct4, color = '4'), size = 0.75) + 
  geom_line(aes(x = lag, y = pct3, color = '3'), size = 0.75) + 
  geom_line(aes(x = lag, y = pct2, color = '2'), size = 0.75) +

POT

get_pot_estimate <- function(par, boot = 500) {
  arr <- 
    foreach (b = 1:boot) %do% {
      mu0 <- rnorm(1, mean = par$mle[1], sd = par$se_mle[1])
      mu1 <- rnorm(1, mean = par$mle[2], sd = par$se_mle[2])
      scale <- rnorm(10, mean = par$mle[3], sd = par$se_mle[3])
      scale <- scale[scale>0][1]
      shape <- rnorm(1, mean = par$mle[4], sd = par$se_mle[4])
      
      foreach (x = 1980:2022-1980, .combine = 'rbind') %do% {
        loc <- mu0 + mu1*x
        rgpd(boot, loc, scale, shape)
      }
    }
  arr <- arr %>% 
    abind(along = 2) %>% 
    apply(1, quantile, p = c(0.05,0.5,0.95)) %>% 
    t %>% data.frame %>% setNames(c('q05', 'med', 'q95')) %>% 
    mutate(wy = 1980:2022) 
  return(arr)
}

GEV

POT is for peaks over thresholds, GEV is for block maxima

get_gev_estimate <- function(par, boot = 500) {
  arr <- 
    foreach (b = 1:boot) %do% {
      mu0 <- rnorm(1, mean = par$mle[1], sd = par$se_mle[1])
      mu1 <- rnorm(1, mean = par$mle[2], sd = par$se_mle[2])
      scale <- rnorm(10, mean = par$mle[3], sd = par$se_mle[3])
      scale <- scale[scale>0][1]
      shape <- rnorm(1, mean = par$mle[4], sd = par$se_mle[4])
      
      foreach (x = 1980:2022-1980, .combine = 'rbind') %do% {
        loc <- mu0 + mu1*x
        rgev(boot, loc, scale, shape)
      }
    }
  arr <- arr %>% 
    abind(along = 2) %>% 
    apply(1, quantile, p = c(0.05,0.25,0.5,0.75,0.95)) %>% 
    t %>% data.frame %>% setNames(c('q05', 'q25', 'med', 'q75', 'q95')) %>% 
    mutate(wy = 1980:2022) 
  return(arr)
}
